'''Simon Bokoté Banza''' (born 13 August 1996) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[UAE Pro League]] side [[Al Jazira Club|Al Jazira]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]].

Formed at [[RC Lens|Lens]], where he played 98 games and scored 16 goals including in [[Ligue 1]] and [[Ligue 2]], he went on to play in Portugal's Primeira Liga for [[F.C. Famalicão|Famalicão]] and Braga. Shortly after making his senior international debut, he was chosen for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]].

==Club career==
===Lens===
Born in [[Creil]], [[Oise]], Banza began his senior career with [[RC Lens|Lens]], first with its [[reserve team]] in the [[Championnat National 2|fourth tier]]. He scored his first [[Ligue 2]] goal on 6 May 2016, as consolation at the end of a 2–1 loss at [[Football Bourg-en-Bresse Péronnas 01|Bourg-en-Bresse]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Simon Banza, de l’AFC Creil au RC Lens |trans-title=Simon Banza, from AFC Creil to RC Lens|url=https://premium.courrier-picard.fr/id53933/article/2019-12-04/simon-banza-de-lafc-creil-au-rc-lens |access-date=8 November 2021 |work=Courrier Picard |date=4 December 2019 |language=French}}</ref>

In January 2017, Banza was loaned to [[Championnat National]] club [[AS Béziers (2007)|Béziers]] until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Football / National : Béziers recrute l'attaquant du RC Lens Simon Banza|trans-title=Football / National: Béziers recruit RC Lens attacker Simon Banza |url=https://www.midilibre.fr/2017/01/09/l-asb-reprend-et-recrute-un-nouvel-attaquant,1450076.php |access-date=8 November 2021 |work=[[Midi Libre]] |date=9 January 2017 |language=French}}</ref> That August, he moved to [[Union Titus Pétange|UT Pétange]] of the [[Luxembourg National Division]] in the same manner.<ref>{{cite news |title=Simon Banza no Union Titus Pétange por empréstimo do Lens|trans-title=Simon Banza to Union Titus Pétange on loan from Lens |url=https://www.wort.lu/pt/latina/simon-banza-no-union-titus-petange-por-emprestimo-do-lens-5be185df182b657ad3b9833e |access-date=8 November 2021 |work=[[Luxemburger Wort]] |date=1 August 2017 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> He was the season's sixth highest scorer with 13 goals, including a [[hat-trick]] in a 4–1 home win over [[US Esch|Esch]] on 15 April 2018.<ref>{{cite news |title=Triplé pour Simon Banza contre l’US Esch|trans-title=Hat-trick for Simon Banza against US Esch |url=https://www.madeinlens.com/actualite-rclens/saison-2017-2018/rc-lens/43384-triple-pour-simon-banza-contre-l-us-esch.html |access-date=8 November 2021 |publisher=Made in Lens |date=17 April 2018 |language=French}}</ref>

On 24 May 2019, Banza scored the extra-time winner as Lens won 2–1 at [[ES Troyes AC|Troyes]] in the second leg of the play-off semi-finals.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Noé |first1=Sébastien |title=Ligue 2 Lens résiste à tout et s’offre une semaine de tous les rêves|trans-title=Ligue 2 Lens resist everything and offer themselves a dream week |url=https://www.lavoixdunord.fr/588233/article/2019-05-24/lens-reve-de-ligue-1-et-defie-troyes-en-barrage-suivez-notre-direct |access-date=8 November 2021 |work=[[La Voix du Nord (daily)|La Voix du Nord]] |date=24 May 2019 |language=French}}</ref> The following season, he scored seven times as Lens won promotion as runners-up, including two on 3 December 2019 in a 3–0 home win over his local side [[FC Chambly|Chambly]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Melosci |first1=Vincent |title=Ligue 2 : Chambly corrigé à Lens|trans-title=Ligue 2: Chambly put right at Lens |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/oise/ligue-2-chambly-corrige-a-lens-03-12-2019-8209383.php |access-date=9 November 2021 |work=[[Le Parisien]] |date=3 December 2019 |language=French}}</ref> He was sent off 18 days later in a 1–0 win over [[Chamois Niortais F.C.|Niort]] also at the [[Stade Bollaert-Delelis]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Le RC Lens champion d'automne après sa victoire face à Niort|trans-title=RC Lens autumn champions after their victory against Niort |url=https://france3-regions.francetvinfo.fr/hauts-de-france/rc-lens-champion-automne-apres-sa-victoire-face-niort-1765911.html |access-date=9 November 2021 |publisher=[[France 3]] |date=21 December 2019 |language=French}}</ref>

===Famalicão===
On 31 August 2021, Banza joined [[F.C. Famalicão|Famalicão]] in Portugal on loan for the [[2021–22 Primeira Liga|2021–22 season]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Simon Banza reforça ataque do Famalicão|trans-title=Simon Banza bolsters Famalicão's attack|url=https://ominho.pt/simon-banza-reforca-ataque-do-famalicao/ |access-date=9 November 2021 |work=O Minho |date=31 August 2021 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> On his [[Primeira Liga]] debut 12 days later, he scored twice in a 2–2 draw at [[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense]];<ref>{{cite news |title=Banza estreia-se com dois golos no empate do Famalicão em Moreira de Cónegos|trans-title=Banza debuts with two goals in Famalicão's draw in Moreira de Cónegos|work=O Minho |url=https://ominho.pt/banza-estreia-se-com-dois-golos-no-empate-do-famalicao-em-moreira-de-conegos/ |access-date=9 November 2021 |date=12 September 2021 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> he added both goals of a win at [[C.D. Santa Clara|Santa Clara]] on 23 October, though he was also sent off.<ref>{{cite news |title=‘Bis’ de Banza dá primeiro triunfo ao Famalicão na Liga|trans-title=Banza brace gives Famalicão first triumph of Liga season|url=https://ominho.pt/bis-de-banza-da-primeiro-triunfo-ao-famalicao-na-liga/ |access-date=9 November 2021 |work=O Minho |date=23 October 2021 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> He finished the season as joint seventh top scorer with 14 goals in 29 games,<ref>{{cite news |title=Darwin Núñez é o melhor marcador da Liga, Taremi em segundo|trans-title=Darwin Núñez is the Liga top scorer, Taremi in second|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/benfica/fc-porto/darwin-nunez-e-o-melhor-marcador-da-liga-taremi-em-segundo |access-date=23 May 2022 |publisher=Mais Futebol |date=15 May 2022 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> including two on the final day in a 3–2 home comeback win over neighbours [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] to ensure a top-half finish.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Farr |first1=Jamie |title=PortuGOAL Figure of the Week: Banza brace fires Famalicão to top eight finish |url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/2587-portugoal-figure-of-the-week-banza-brace-fires-famalicao-to-top-eight-finish |access-date=23 May 2022 |publisher=PortuGOAL |date=16 May 2022}}</ref>

===Braga===
On 19 July 2022, Banza signed a five-year deal with Braga for a €3 million fee, complete with a [[buyout clause]] of €30 million.<ref>{{cite news |title=Avançado Simon Banza reforça Sp. Braga|trans-title=Forward Simon Banza bolsters Sp. Braga|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/avancado-simon-banza-reforca-sp-braga-15030849.html |access-date=19 July 2022 |work=[[Diário de Notícias]] |date=19 July 2022 |language=Portuguese}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Pereira |first1=Sérgio |title=Sp. Braga garante Simon Banza por três milhões de euros|trans-title=Sp. Braga confirm Simon Banza for three million euros|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/sp-braga/transferencias/sp-braga-garante-simon-banza-por-tres-milhoes-de-euros |access-date=19 July 2022 |publisher=Mais Futebol |date=19 July 2022 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> He made his debut on 7 August in the season opener at home to [[Sporting CP]], scoring his club's first goal of a 3–3 draw;<ref>{{cite news |last1=Antunes |first1=Inês |title=SC Braga e Sporting empataram, mas o futebol saiu vencedor|trans-title=SC Braga and Sporting drew, but football emerged the winner |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira-liga/artigos/sc-braga-e-sporting-empataram-mas-o-futebol-saiu-vencedor |access-date=8 August 2022 |publisher=SAPO |date=7 August 2020 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> five days later he added two more goals in a 3–0 win on his return to Famalicão.<ref>{{cite news |title=Banza bisa no regresso a Famalicão e dá primeira vitória ao Braga|trans-title=Banza scores brace on return to Famalicão and gives first victory to Braga|url=https://rr.sapo.pt/bola-branca/noticia/futebol-nacional/2022/08/12/banza-bisa-no-regresso-a-famalicao-e-da-primeira-vitoria-ao-braga/295750/ |access-date=14 August 2022 |publisher=[[Rádio Renascença]] |date=12 August 2022 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> In the [[2023–24 Primeira Liga|2023–24 season]], he managed to score 21 goals in the Primeira Liga, equalling his club's top scorer in a single campaign, [[Chico Gordo]] in the 1977–78 season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.digitalcongo.net/article-en/soccer-with-23-goals-in-23-matches-congolese-striker-simon-banza-dazzles-in-portugal/ |title=Soccer: With 23 goals in 23 matches, Congolese striker Simon Banza dazzles in Portugal |publisher=Digitalcongo.net |date=3 April 2024 }}</ref>

==== Trabzonspor ====
On 13 September 2024, Banza signed for Turkish club [[Trabzonspor]] on a one-year loan deal.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Trabzonspor, Simon Banza ile 1 yıllık sözleşme imzaladı |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/tr/futbol/trabzonspor-simon-banza-ile-1-yillik-sozlesme-imzaladi/3329545 |access-date=2024-09-17 |website=www.aa.com.tr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Trabzonspor |first= |title=Yeni transferimiz Simon Banza ile sözleşme imzaladık |url=https://www.trabzonspor.org.tr/tr/haberler/guncel-haberler/yeni-transferimiz-simon-banza-ile-sozlesme-imzaladik-13-09-2024 |access-date=2024-09-17 |website=www.trabzonspor.org.tr |language=tr}}</ref>

==== Al Jazira ====
On 22 September 2025, Banza signed for Emirati club [[Al Jazira Club|Al Jazira]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=الجزيرة يبرم صفقة من الدوري البرتغالي|url=https://www.kooora.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D8%B2%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D8%A8%D8%B1%D9%85-%D8%B5%D9%81%D9%82%D8%A9-%D9%85%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%AA%D8%BA%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A/blt67515d6fcf515658}}</ref>

== International career ==
Banza was born in France to [[Democratic Republic of the Congo|DR Congolese]] parents.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Enyimo |first1=Martin |title=Ligue 2 française : des RD-Congolais de souche titulaires en clubs en première journée |trans-title=French Ligue 1: players of DR Congolese origin start for clubs on opening day|url=http://www.adiac-congo.com/content/ligue-2-francaise-des-rd-congolais-de-souche-titulaires-en-clubs-en-premiere-journee-54448 |access-date=9 November 2021 |publisher=[[Agence d'Information d'Afrique Centrale]] |date=3 August 2016 |language=French}}</ref> On 2 October 2023, he was called up to the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]] for a set of friendlies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.afrik-foot.com/rdc-liste-leopards-desabre-angola-nouvelle-zelande-octobre-2023-bertaud-diangana|title=RDC : la liste d'octobre avec un ancien Lensois, un nouveau de L1 et un ex-international Espoirs anglais !|trans-title=DRC: the October list with a former Lens player, a new L1 player and a former England under-21 international!|date=2 October 2023|website=www.afrik-foot.com|language=French}}</ref> He made his debut 11 days later in a 1–1 draw with [[New Zealand men's national football team|New Zealand]] in [[Murcia]], Spain, playing the final 11 minutes as a substitute for [[Cédric Bakambu]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Banza estreou-se com a camisola da RD Congo|trans-title=Banza debuted in the DR Congo shirt|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-betclic/sp--braga/detalhe/banza-estreou-se-com-a-camisola-da-rd-congo |access-date=24 January 2024 |work=Record |date=13 October 2023 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> He was chosen for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] at the start of the following year, in the Ivory Coast.<ref>{{cite news |title=Banza convocado para a CAN, falha jogos com os três grandes|trans-title=Banza chosen for AFCON, misses games with big three|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/4716534266/banza-convocado-para-a-can-falha-jogos-com-os-tres-grandes/ |access-date=24 January 2024 |work=O Jogo |date=27 December 2023 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>

